mutant: m025_compaction_overdrop_above_watermark
target: internal/ingest/orchestrator/compact_deletes.go
failure-mode: |
  The compaction pass folds each decoded block with an UNBOUNDED high seq
  (FoldRange(events, watermark, ^uint64(0))) instead of the pass's bounded
  (watermark, targetWatermark] window. A block that STRADDLES the watermark
  (MinSeq <= W < MaxSeq) is decoded by the pass; with the upper bound removed, a
  delete at seq > targetWatermark inside that straddling block folds into the
  snapshot and suppresses its own create — a create at/below the watermark that
  the pass should have KEPT (its only superseding tombstone is above W, so the
  create is still a legitimate survivor of THIS pass). A convergence-hiding
  compaction over-drop: a survivor the window says must remain is wrongly
  removed.

  (History: before #178 this failure mode lived in the in-memory
  Set.SnapshotRange(current, ^uint64(0)) readout; step 5 deleted that overlay-only
  method and compaction now folds the on-disk window via FoldRange, so the mutant
  was re-expressed against FoldRange's upper bound — the same over-drop, same
  detection contract.)
expected-detection: |
  Killed by the metamorphic compactionOverDropRecorder.Assert at
  steady-state-shutdown-flush in TestOracle_DefaultLifecycle (full lifecycle,
  not -short), with "compaction over-drop at watermark=W".

  This mutant proves the UNIQUE power of the #100 over-drop check that the
  blanket m024 mutant does NOT exercise: the dropped create's record is
  independently deleted ABOVE the watermark, so the record is absent in final
  state either way and final-state Compare stays GREEN. Only the pre/post
  metamorphic recorder — which holds the pass to "every survivor the documented
  filter says must remain at W is still present after the pass" — catches it.
  (Contrast m024, caught by final-state because it also drops rows still live.)

  A straddle (create <= W, delete > W in one block) is the normal steady-state
  shape; the bug is letting an above-W tombstone act on an at/below-W survivor.
  SURVIVES -short (too little steady traffic to materialize a straddle + pass),
  so this mutant's home is the stress tier.
expected-tier: stress
tiers: stress

diff --git a/internal/ingest/orchestrator/compact_deletes.go b/internal/ingest/orchestrator/compact_deletes.go
--- a/internal/ingest/orchestrator/compact_deletes.go
+++ b/internal/ingest/orchestrator/compact_deletes.go
@@ -305 +305 @@ func (o *Orchestrator) collectCompactionTombstones(ctx context.Context, sealed [
-			part, err := tombstone.FoldRange(events, watermark, targetWatermark)
+			part, err := tombstone.FoldRange(events, watermark, ^uint64(0))
